{"lemma":"بَتَّةُ","slug":"بَتَّةُ","root":"ب.ت.ت","root_slug":"ب-ت-ت","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ت-ت","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1690","n1695"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%AA%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"instance noun of بَتّ (batt, “decision”)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"used in the adverbial accusative in a way which can be translated as “absolutely”, “at all”, “definitely”, ”decisively”"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/bat.ta/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1690","headword_ar":"بَتَّهُ","root":"bt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, T, S, M, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb,) the latter anomalous, because a reduplicative verb [of this kind] having the aor. with kesr is not trans., except in certain instances, of which this is one; the other instances being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~ahu","text_ar":"عَلَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in relation to drinking, aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nam~a","text_ar":"نَمَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHadiyva","text_ar":"الحَدِيثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ad~ahu","text_ar":"شَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~ahu","text_ar":"حَبَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; the last having but one form [of aor.]; (S;) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bat~N","text_ar":"بَتٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lth, T, S, M, A, &c.:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abt~hu","text_ar":"ابتّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibotaAtN","text_ar":"اـِبْتَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cut it off, severed it, separated it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disunited it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, S, M, A, * Mgh, * Msb, K, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"entirely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"utterly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, M;) namely, a thing; (M;) a rope, or cord; (Lth, T;) and a tie, or bond, of union between two persons. (M.) ―         -b2-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bat~ahu","text_ar":"بَتَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abt~hu","text_ar":"ابتّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to the TA, app. signify also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, caused him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to become unable to proceed in his journey, his camel that bore him breaking down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stopping from fatigue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perishing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Anbt~","text_ar":"انبتّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying “he became so” is there said to be quasi-pass. of those two verbs when it has this sense. Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bat~ahu Als~afaru","text_ar":"بَتَّهُ السَّفَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The journey caused him to become cut off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAqa daAb~atahu Hat~ay bat~ahaA","text_ar":"سَاقَ دَابَّتَهُ حَتَّي بَتَّهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He urged on his beast so that,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until, he caused it to become cut off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (A:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEiyrahu","text_ar":"بَعِيرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abat~a","text_ar":"اَبَتَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He caused his camel to become cut off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTaEapu","text_ar":"قَطَعَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by travel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) this is not said but of a man who has forced on his camel at a hard pace, or by laborious journeying. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bat~a TalaAqa A@moraA^atihi","text_ar":"بَتَّ طَلَاقَ ا@مْرَاَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, Msb, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TalaAqa AlmaroA^api","text_ar":"طَلَاقَ المَرْاَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abat~ahu","text_ar":"اَبَتَّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, T, Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made the divorce of his wife,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the woman, to be absolutely separating,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, Mgh, Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to cut her off from return."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) Lth, with whom AZ agrees, has erred in asserting that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bat~a","text_ar":"بَتَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is intrans. and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abat~","text_ar":"اَبَتّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"trans.: (T, TA:) both are trans. and intrans., (T, Msb, TA,) as En-Nawawee asserts in the Tahdheeb el-Asmà wa-1-Loghát. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~aloqapu AlwaAHidapu tabut~u","text_ar":"الطَّلْقَةُ الوَاحِدَةُ تَبُتُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tubit~u","text_ar":"تُبِتُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The single divorce cuts the matrimonial tie,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bond, of the woman,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqoTaEu EiSomapa Aln~ikaAHi","text_ar":"تَقْطَعُ عِصْمَةَ النِّكَاحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", T, Mgh, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when the period during which she must wait before contracting a new marriage has ended."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bat~N","text_ar":"بَتٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bat~a Ealayohi AlqaDaA='a","text_ar":"بَتَّ عَلَيْهِ القَضَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, A,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bat~N","text_ar":"بَتٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abat~ahu","text_ar":"اَبَتَّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, S, M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the judge, T)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"decided the judgment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sentence, against him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, * M.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bat~a Ealayohi Al$~ahaAdapa","text_ar":"بَتَّ عَلَيْهِ الشَّهَادَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abat~ahaA","text_ar":"اَبَتَّهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He decided against him by the testimony,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pronounced the testimony decisive against him,] and compelled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constrained, him to admit it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bat~a $ahaAdatahu","text_ar":"بَتَّ شَهَادَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abat~ahaA","text_ar":"اَبَتَّهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave his testimony decisively."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abut~u A^an~ahu qaAla","text_ar":"اَبُتُّ اَنَّهُ قَالَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I know,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"declare, decidedly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"not [merely] thinking it,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that he said"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus. (Saheeh of Muslim.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bat~a Aln~iy~apa","text_ar":"بَتَّ النِّيَّةَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made the intention decided;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fixed it decidedly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA SiyaAma limano","text_ar":"لَا صِيَامَ لِمَنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~yaAmi mina All~ayoli","text_ar":"الصّيَامِ مِنَ اللَّيْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo yubit~a","text_ar":"لَمْ يُبِتَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo yabut~a","text_ar":"لَمْ يَبُتَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to different recitals, (Mgh,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is no fasting to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his fasting is null] who does not decisively impose it upon himself, by intention, from the night:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Mgh:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who does not form the intention of fasting before daybreak, and thus cut it off from the time in which there is no fasting, namely, the night:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the intention is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bat~N","text_ar":"بَتٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibotaAtN","text_ar":"اـِبْتَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] because it makes a division between non-fasting and fasting: (T, TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo yubit","text_ar":"لَمْ يُبِت"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_ibaAtapu","text_ar":"الاـِبَاتَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is a mistake; but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lm yubay~it","text_ar":"لم يُبَيِّت"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~aboyiytu","text_ar":"التَّبْيِيتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bay~ata","text_ar":"بَيَّتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] is correct. (Mgh.) And it is said in another trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nikaAHa h`*ihi Aln~isaA='i","text_ar":"نِكَاحَ هٰذِهِ النِّسَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abit~uwA","text_ar":"اَبِتُّوا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Decide ye the affair respecting the marriage of these women, and confirm it by its [proper] conditions:"},{"kind":"text","text":"an oblique prohibition of the kind of marriage termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nikaAHu AlmutoEapi","text_ar":"نِكَاحُ المُتْعَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because it is a marriage not [absolutely or lawfully] decided, [being] made definite as to duration. (TA.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bat~a","text_ar":"بَتَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made to have,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"take, effect; he executed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"performed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 210;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abt~","text_ar":"ابتّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abt~ yamiynahu","text_ar":"ابتّ يَمِينَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made his oath to have,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"take, effect; he executed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"performed, it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakoriAnu maA yabut~u kalaAmFA","text_ar":"سَكْرِانُ مَا يَبُتُّ كَلَامًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Ks, T, M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA yabit~u","text_ar":"ما يَبِتُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA yubit~u","text_ar":"ما يُبِتُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Ks, T, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who is drunk, who does not speak plainly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distinctly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who does not make speech plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distinct;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, T;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who does not articulate speech;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA yaqoTaEuhu","text_ar":"مَا يَقْطَعُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) or,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":148},{"kind":"text","text":"as As says, (T,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakoraAnu maA yabut~u","text_ar":"سَكْرَانُ مَا يَبُتُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, A,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yabut~u","text_ar":"لَا يَبُتُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA yabit~u","text_ar":"لا يَبِتُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA yubat~u","text_ar":"لا يُبَتُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) which last form of the verb is disallowed by As, but both are correct accord. to Fr, (T, S,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who is drunk, who does not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cannot,] decide an affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, T, S, K.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAt~N","text_ar":"بَاتٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-  See also 7. ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bat~to yamiynuhu","text_ar":"بَتّتْ يَمِينُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"only, inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"butuwtN","text_ar":"بُتُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His oath bad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took, effect; was executed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"performed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajabato","text_ar":"وَجَبَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proved, true:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) a phrase mentioned by AZ, and, if correct, not needing any explanation. (M.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abt~ yamiynahu","text_ar":"ابتّ يَمِينَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", above.]       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bat~a","text_ar":"بَتَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"butuwtN","text_ar":"بُتُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, lean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meagre."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAt~N","text_ar":"بَاتٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bat~N","text_ar":"بَتٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bat~a","text_ar":"بَتَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"selling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weaving, a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garment of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TayolasaAn","text_ar":"طَيْلَسَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bat~","text_ar":"بَتّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]. (KL.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Msb","Mgh","K","A","TA","T","Lth","Ks"]},{"entry_id":"n1695","headword_ar":"بَتَّةٌ","root":"bt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bat~N","text_ar":"بَتٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A^afoEaluhu A@lobat~apa","text_ar":"لَا اَفْعَلُهُ ا@لْبَتَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bat~apF","text_ar":"بَتَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) the latter mentioned by IF, (Msb,) but IB says that Sb and his companions allow only the former, and that only Fr allows the latter, (TA,) and some say that the former has been heard pronounced with the disjunctive. ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aalobat~apa","text_ar":"اَلْبَتَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (MF,) and thus it is written in a copy of the K, (TA,) but others greatly disapprove of this, (MF,) [meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not do it, decidedly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"absolutely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said of anything in respect of which there is no returning, or revoking; (S, IF, M, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alabt~apa","text_ar":"الَبتَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being said of a thing to be done, or performed, irrevocably, and from which there is no abstaining by reason of sluggishness; (T;) as though the speaker cut off the doing of the thing: (M:) the last word is in the accus. case as an inf. n.: (S:) Sb says, it is a corroborative inf. n., and is not used without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHosibuhu qaAla juwayoriyap A^awi A@lobapa qaAla","text_ar":"اَحْسِبُهُ قَالَ جُوَيْرِيَة اَوِ ا@لْبَةَ قَالَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I think he said Juweyriyeh, or decidedly he said so"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as though the speaker doubted of the female's name, and said, “ I think it was Juweyriyeh; ” then corrected, and said, “ or I know, ” or “ declare, ” “ decidedly, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abut~u","text_ar":"اَبُتُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqoTaEu","text_ar":"اَقْطَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) that he said Juweyriyeh: I do not [merely] think. ” (Saheeh of Muslim.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","Msb","TA","MF"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}